verses.text_plain: The word of the Lord came again unto me, saying,
verses.verse_html: 1The word of the Lord came again unto me, saying,

verses.text_plain: Now, thou son of man, take up a lamentation for Tyrus;
verses.verse_html: 2Now, thou son of man, take up a lamentation for Tyrus;

verses.text_plain: And say unto Tyrus, O thou that art situate at the entry of the sea, which art a merchant of the people for many isles, Thus saith the Lord God; O Tyrus, thou hast said, I am of perfect beauty.
verses.verse_html:
3And say unto Tyrus, O thou that art situate at the entry of the sea, which art a merchant of the people for many isles, Thus saith the Lord God; O Tyrus, thou hast said, I am of perfect beauty. ▼
▼ of perfect…: Heb. perfect of beauty

footnotes.body_text: ▼ of perfect…: Heb. perfect of beauty
footnotes.body_html: ▼ of perfect…: Heb. perfect of beauty

verses.text_plain: Thy borders are in the midst of the seas, thy builders have perfected thy beauty.
verses.verse_html:
4Thy borders are in the midst of the seas, thy builders have perfected thy beauty. ▼
▼ midst: Heb. heart

footnotes.body_html: ▼ midst: Heb. heart

verses.text_plain: They have made all thy ship boards of fir trees of Senir: they have taken cedars from Lebanon to make masts for thee.
verses.verse_html:
5They have made all thy ship boards of fir trees of Senir: they have taken cedars from Lebanon to make masts for thee. ▼
▼ made: Heb. built

footnotes.body_html: ▼ made: Heb. built

verses.text_plain: Of the oaks of Bashan have they made thine oars; the company of the Ashurites have made thy benches of ivory, brought out of the isles of Chittim.
verses.verse_html:
6Of the oaks of Bashan have they made thine oars; the company of the Ashurites have made thy benches of ivory, brought out of the isles of Chittim. ▼
▼ the company…: or, they have made thy hatches of ivory well trodden
 , ▼
▼ company: Heb. daughter

footnotes.body_text: ▼ the company…: or, they have made thy hatches of ivory well trodden
footnotes.body_html: ▼ the company…: or, they have made thy hatches of ivory well trodden
▼ company: Heb. daughter

verses.text_plain: Fine linen with broidered work from Egypt was that which thou spreadest forth to be thy sail; blue and purple from the isles of Elishah was that which covered thee.
verses.verse_html:
7Fine linen with broidered work from Egypt was that which thou spreadest forth to be thy sail; blue and purple from the isles of Elishah was that which covered thee. ▼
▼ blue…: or, purple and scarlet

tokens.text: was that which thou spreadest forth

footnotes.body_html: ▼ blue…: or, purple and scarlet

verses.text_plain: The inhabitants of Zidon and Arvad were thy mariners: thy wise men, O Tyrus, that were in thee, were thy pilots.
verses.verse_html: 8The inhabitants of Zidon and Arvad were thy mariners: thy wise men, O Tyrus, that were in thee, were thy pilots.

tokens.text: were in thee, were thy pilots

verses.text_plain: The ancients of Gebal and the wise men thereof were in thee thy calkers: all the ships of the sea with their mariners were in thee to occupy thy merchandise.
verses.verse_html:
9The ancients of Gebal and the wise men thereof were in thee thy calkers: all the ships of the sea with their mariners were in thee to occupy thy merchandise. ▼
▼ calkers: or, stoppers of chinks: Heb. strengtheners, etc

tokens.text: thereof were in thee thy calkers

footnotes.body_text: ▼ calkers: or, stoppers of chinks: Heb. strengtheners, etc
footnotes.body_html: ▼ calkers: or, stoppers of chinks: Heb. strengtheners, etc

verses.text_plain: They of Persia and of Lud and of Phut were in thine army, thy men of war: they hanged the shield and helmet in thee; they set forth thy comeliness.
verses.verse_html: 10They of Persia and of Lud and of Phut were in thine army, thy men of war: they hanged the shield and helmet in thee; they set forth thy comeliness.

verses.text_plain: The men of Arvad with thine army were upon thy walls round about, and the Gammadims were in thy towers: they hanged their shields upon thy walls round about; they have made thy beauty perfect.
verses.verse_html: 11The men of Arvad with thine army were upon thy walls round about, and the Gammadims were in thy towers: they hanged their shields upon thy walls round about; they have made thy beauty perfect.

verses.text_plain: Tarshish was thy merchant by reason of the multitude of all kind of riches; with silver, iron, tin, and lead, they traded in thy fairs.
verses.verse_html: 12Tarshish was thy merchant by reason of the multitude of all kind of riches; with silver, iron, tin, and lead, they traded in thy fairs.

verses.text_plain: Javan, Tubal, and Meshech, they were thy merchants: they traded the persons of men and vessels of brass in thy market.
verses.verse_html:
13Javan, Tubal, and Meshech, they were thy merchants: they traded the persons of men and vessels of brass in thy market. ▼
▼ market: or, merchandise

footnotes.body_html: ▼ market: or, merchandise

verses.text_plain: They of the house of Togarmah traded in thy fairs with horses and horsemen and mules.
verses.verse_html: 14They of the house of Togarmah traded in thy fairs with horses and horsemen and mules.

verses.text_plain: The men of Dedan were thy merchants; many isles were the merchandise of thine hand: they brought thee for a present horns of ivory and ebony.
verses.verse_html: 15The men of Dedan were thy merchants; many isles were the merchandise of thine hand: they brought thee for a present horns of ivory and ebony.

verses.text_plain: Syria was thy merchant by reason of the multitude of the wares of thy making: they occupied in thy fairs with emeralds, purple, and broidered work, and fine linen, and coral, and agate.
verses.verse_html:
16Syria was thy merchant by reason of the multitude of the wares of thy making: they occupied in thy fairs with emeralds, purple, and broidered work, and fine linen, and coral, and agate. ▼
▼ the wares…: Heb. thy works
 , ▼
▼ agate: or, chrysoprase

tokens.text: of the wares of thy making

footnotes.body_html: ▼ the wares…: Heb. thy works
▼ agate: or, chrysoprase

verses.text_plain: Judah, and the land of Israel, they were thy merchants: they traded in thy market wheat of Minnith, and Pannag, and honey, and oil, and balm.
verses.verse_html:
17Judah, and the land of Israel, they were thy merchants: they traded in thy market wheat of Minnith, and Pannag, and honey, and oil, and balm. ▼
▼ balm: or, rosin

footnotes.body_html: ▼ balm: or, rosin

verses.text_plain: Damascus was thy merchant in the multitude of the wares of thy making, for the multitude of all riches; in the wine of Helbon, and white wool.
verses.verse_html: 18Damascus was thy merchant in the multitude of the wares of thy making, for the multitude of all riches; in the wine of Helbon, and white wool.

tokens.text: of the wares of thy making

verses.text_plain: Dan also and Javan going to and fro occupied in thy fairs: bright iron, cassia, and calamus, were in thy market.
verses.verse_html:
19Dan also and Javan going to and fro occupied in thy fairs: bright iron, cassia, and calamus, were in thy market. ▼
▼ going…: or, Meuzal

footnotes.body_html: ▼ going…: or, Meuzal

verses.text_plain: Dedan was thy merchant in precious clothes for chariots.
verses.verse_html:
20Dedan was thy merchant in precious clothes for chariots. ▼
▼ precious…: Heb. clothes of freedom

footnotes.body_html: ▼ precious…: Heb. clothes of freedom

verses.text_plain: Arabia, and all the princes of Kedar, they occupied with thee in lambs, and rams, and goats: in these were they thy merchants.
verses.verse_html:
21Arabia, and all the princes of Kedar, they occupied with thee in lambs, and rams, and goats: in these were they thy merchants. ▼
▼ they occupied…: Heb. they were the merchants of thy hand

footnotes.body_text: ▼ they occupied…: Heb. they were the merchants of thy hand
footnotes.body_html: ▼ they occupied…: Heb. they were the merchants of thy hand

verses.text_plain: The merchants of Sheba and Raamah, they were thy merchants: they occupied in thy fairs with chief of all spices, and with all precious stones, and gold.
verses.verse_html: 22The merchants of Sheba and Raamah, they were thy merchants: they occupied in thy fairs with chief of all spices, and with all precious stones, and gold.

verses.text_plain: Haran, and Canneh, and Eden, the merchants of Sheba, Asshur, and Chilmad, were thy merchants.
verses.verse_html: 23Haran, and Canneh, and Eden, the merchants of Sheba, Asshur, and Chilmad, were thy merchants.

verses.text_plain: These were thy merchants in all sorts of things, in blue clothes, and broidered work, and in chests of rich apparel, bound with cords, and made of cedar, among thy merchandise.
verses.verse_html:
24These were thy merchants in all sorts of things, in blue clothes, and broidered work, and in chests of rich apparel, bound with cords, and made of cedar, among thy merchandise. ▼
▼ all…: or, excellent things
 , ▼
▼ clothes: Heb. foldings

footnotes.body_html: ▼ all…: or, excellent things
▼ clothes: Heb. foldings

verses.text_plain: The ships of Tarshish did sing of thee in thy market: and thou wast replenished, and made very glorious in the midst of the seas.
verses.verse_html: 25The ships of Tarshish did sing of thee in thy market: and thou wast replenished, and made very glorious in the midst of the seas.

verses.text_plain: Thy rowers have brought thee into great waters: the east wind hath broken thee in the midst of the seas.
verses.verse_html:
26Thy rowers have brought thee into great waters: the east wind hath broken thee in the midst of the seas. ▼
▼ midst: Heb. heart

footnotes.body_html: ▼ midst: Heb. heart

verses.text_plain: Thy riches, and thy fairs, thy merchandise, thy mariners, and thy pilots, thy calkers, and the occupiers of thy merchandise, and all thy men of war, that are in thee, and in all thy company which is in the midst of thee, shall fall into the midst of the seas in the day of thy ruin.
verses.verse_html:
27Thy riches, and thy fairs, thy merchandise, thy mariners, and thy pilots, thy calkers, and the occupiers of thy merchandise, and all thy men of war, that are in thee, and in all thy company which is in the midst of thee, shall fall into the midst of the seas in the day of thy ruin. ▼
▼ and in…: or, even with all
 , ▼
▼ midst of the seas: Heb. heart, etc

tokens.text: in thee, and in all thy company

footnotes.body_html: ▼ midst of the seas: Heb. heart, etc

verses.text_plain: The suburbs shall shake at the sound of the cry of thy pilots.
verses.verse_html:
28The suburbs shall shake at the sound of the cry of thy pilots. ▼
▼ suburbs: or, waves

footnotes.body_html: ▼ suburbs: or, waves

verses.text_plain: And all that handle the oar, the mariners, and all the pilots of the sea, shall come down from their ships, they shall stand upon the land;
verses.verse_html: 29And all that handle the oar, the mariners, and all the pilots of the sea, shall come down from their ships, they shall stand upon the land;

verses.text_plain: And shall cause their voice to be heard against thee, and shall cry bitterly, and shall cast up dust upon their heads, they shall wallow themselves in the ashes:
verses.verse_html: 30And shall cause their voice to be heard against thee, and shall cry bitterly, and shall cast up dust upon their heads, they shall wallow themselves in the ashes:

verses.text_plain: And they shall make themselves utterly bald for thee, and gird them with sackcloth, and they shall weep for thee with bitterness of heart and bitter wailing.
verses.verse_html: 31And they shall make themselves utterly bald for thee, and gird them with sackcloth, and they shall weep for thee with bitterness of heart and bitter wailing.

tokens.text: And they shall make themselves utterly

verses.text_plain: And in their wailing they shall take up a lamentation for thee, and lament over thee, saying, What city is like Tyrus, like the destroyed in the midst of the sea?
verses.verse_html: 32And in their wailing they shall take up a lamentation for thee, and lament over thee, saying, What city is like Tyrus, like the destroyed in the midst of the sea?

verses.text_plain: When thy wares went forth out of the seas, thou filledst many people; thou didst enrich the kings of the earth with the multitude of thy riches and of thy merchandise.
verses.verse_html: 33When thy wares went forth out of the seas, thou filledst many people; thou didst enrich the kings of the earth with the multitude of thy riches and of thy merchandise.

verses.text_plain: In the time when thou shalt be broken by the seas in the depths of the waters thy merchandise and all thy company in the midst of thee shall fall.
verses.verse_html: 34In the time when thou shalt be broken by the seas in the depths of the waters thy merchandise and all thy company in the midst of thee shall fall.

verses.text_plain: All the inhabitants of the isles shall be astonished at thee, and their kings shall be sore afraid, they shall be troubled in their countenance.
verses.verse_html: 35All the inhabitants of the isles shall be astonished at thee, and their kings shall be sore afraid, they shall be troubled in their countenance.

verses.text_plain: The merchants among the people shall hiss at thee; thou shalt be a terror, and never shalt be any more.
verses.verse_html:
36The merchants among the people shall hiss at thee; thou shalt be a terror, and never shalt be any more. ▼

 , ▼
